<b>Did he beat you up?</b>

677
00:49:11,676 --> 00:49:14,115
<b>What? Of course, not.</b>

678
00:49:14,316 --> 00:49:16,586
<b>I was being careless
and ran into something.</b>

679
00:49:16,586 --> 00:49:19,416
<b>Go to my office.
I'll be there soon.</b>

680
00:49:19,615 --> 00:49:20,655
<b>Okay.</b>

681
00:49:25,655 --> 00:49:27,225
<b>You went to the pharmacy?</b>

682
00:49:27,855 --> 00:49:32,125
<b>Hey, you should take better care
of your face.</b>

683
00:49:32,125 --> 00:49:34,235
<b>Why would you walk around
and show it off?</b>

684
00:49:34,235 --> 00:49:37,036
<b>It's not bad.
I even got free ointment.</b>

685
00:49:38,765 --> 00:49:39,775
<b>Seeing how you're joking around,</b>

686
00:49:39,775 --> 00:49:41,405
<b>you're finally back
to being yourself.</b>

687
00:49:42,806 --> 00:49:44,505
<b>I heard Ha Jin is hospitalized.</b>

688
00:49:44,806 --> 00:49:46,475
<b>Did she get hurt?</b>

689
00:49:46,775 --> 00:49:49,015
<b>Fortunately, she's well.</b>

690
00:49:49,316 --> 00:49:50,446
<b>But she must've been shocked.</b>

691
00:49:50,446 --> 00:49:53,515
<b>You're right.
She'll need time to recover.</b>

692
00:49:54,385 --> 00:49:57,056
<b>I'm truly glad
that she's safe and sound.</b>

693
00:49:57,826 --> 00:49:58,826
<b>Me too.</b>

694
00:49:59,286 --> 00:50:01,556
<b>I'm trying my best to cover for you.</b>

695
00:50:03,225 --> 00:50:06,395
<b>But I don't think the higher-ups
will let you off the hook.</b>

696
00:50:07,635 --> 00:50:10,666
<b>No matter what the reason may be,
you did bail on the news.</b>

697
00:50:12,566 --> 00:50:14,005
<b>I know.</b>

698
00:50:14,005 --> 00:50:15,605
<b>Will you be okay today?</b>

699
00:50:16,005 --> 00:50:19,475
<b>You'll have to read news
about Ha Jin.</b>

700
00:50:19,875 --> 00:50:20,875
<b>I'll do it.</b>

701
00:50:21,446 --> 00:50:22,475
<b>Thank you...</b>

702
00:50:23,385 --> 00:50:25,145
<b>for letting me off the hook
last time...</b>

703
00:50:25,245 --> 00:50:26,686
<b>and for yesterday as well.</b>

704
00:50:28,056 --> 00:50:30,056
<b>I'll come to my senses and do well.</b>

705
00:50:30,056 --> 00:50:31,456
<b>Forget it.</b>

706
00:50:32,326 --> 00:50:35,826
<b>Tell the makeup artist
to cover that up well.</b>

707
00:50:37,465 --> 00:50:38,496
<b>Okay.</b>

708
00:50:38,665 --> 00:50:39,766
<b>You may leave.</b>

709
00:50:39,766 --> 00:50:41,695
<b>- I'll be going, then.
- Okay.</b>

710
00:50:42,236 --> 00:50:44,036
<b>- Hey.
- Thank you.</b>

711
00:50:53,816 --> 00:50:56,816
<b>- Hey, you were here.
- Yes.</b>

712
00:50:56,816 --> 00:50:58,445
<b>Did you watch the news
about Director Ji?</b>

713
00:50:59,546 --> 00:51:00,786
<b>It was a good one.</b>

714
00:51:02,486 --> 00:51:05,385
<b>Who taught you to reveal
a culprit's identity like that?</b>

715
00:51:05,385 --> 00:51:07,125
<b>Whom do you think?</b>

716
00:51:07,125 --> 00:51:10,465
<b>I'm your one and only junior.</b>

717
00:51:10,465 --> 00:51:14,165
<b>The entire world ought to know
who abducted our dear Ha Jin.</b>

718
00:51:14,165 --> 00:51:15,665
<b>- "Our dear Ha Jin"?
- Yes.</b>

719
00:51:15,695 --> 00:51:17,066
<b>You two must be close.</b>

720
00:51:17,365 --> 00:51:21,135
<b>Of course. I just got back
from her surprise birthday party.</b>

721
00:51:21,476 --> 00:51:23,145
<b>She had a surprise birthday party?</b>

722
00:51:23,145 --> 00:51:25,175
<b>Yes, I went with Ha Kyung...</b>

723
00:51:27,645 --> 00:51:31,145
<b>I visited the hospital
with Ha Kyung...</b>

724
00:51:31,145 --> 00:51:32,445
<b>and had a small party.</b>

725
00:51:32,945 --> 00:51:35,455
<b>She looks much better now.</b>

726
00:51:35,556 --> 00:51:36,955
<b>Really?</b>

727
00:51:37,226 --> 00:51:39,625
<b>I should go work.</b>

728
00:51:39,625 --> 00:51:40,625
<b>Sure.</b>

729
00:51:54,336 --> 00:51:55,435
<b>I'm Reporter Lee Ji Jeong.</b>

730
00:51:55,806 --> 00:51:59,076
<b>Director Ji Hyun Geun, who stalked
and abducted actress Yeo Ha Jin,</b>

731
00:51:59,076 --> 00:52:00,615
<b>was arrested.</b>

732
00:52:00,746 --> 00:52:03,115
<b>He broke into her house...</b>

733
00:52:03,115 --> 00:52:04,846
<b>and stalked her continuously.</b>

734
00:52:04,846 --> 00:52:06,046
<b>He's currently under arrest...</b>

735
00:52:06,046 --> 00:52:08,385
<b>for locking her up
in his villa in Gyeonggi Province.</b>

736
00:52:08,816 --> 00:52:10,925
<b>He claimed to have committed
the crime because his love...</b>

737
00:52:10,925 --> 00:52:13,195
<b>- Lee Jeong Hoon...
- was unreciprocated.</b>

738
00:52:13,195 --> 00:52:14,395
<b>caught him, indeed.</b>

739
00:52:14,395 --> 00:52:15,855
<b>After being rescued,
Yeo Ha Jin fainted...</b>

740
00:52:23,066 --> 00:52:24,165
<b>Who are you?</b>

741
00:52:25,635 --> 00:52:27,276
<b>Why did you want to see me?</b>

742
00:52:27,675 --> 00:52:29,476
<b>I'll tell you that later.</b>

743
00:52:29,476 --> 00:52:32,445
<b>But first, you're the one
who killed Ms. Jung Seo Yeon, right?</b>

744
00:52:36,786 --> 00:52:37,816
<b>Who are you?</b>

745
00:52:37,816 --> 00:52:39,685
<b>Don't be so cold.
We're on the same team.</b>

746
00:52:40,215 --> 00:52:41,855
<b>Who are you?</b>

747
00:52:41,855 --> 00:52:42,915
<b>I see.</b>

748
00:52:42,915 --> 00:52:45,226
<b>You must be in the dark about
what Lee Jeong Hoon has been up...</b>

749
00:52:45,226 --> 00:52:46,556
<b>being locked up in here.</b>

750
00:52:46,925 --> 00:52:47,925
<b>Hold on.</b>

751
00:52:50,665 --> 00:52:52,066
<b>("Yeo Ha Jin's New Boyfriend,
Lee Jeong Hoon")</b>

752
00:52:54,996 --> 00:52:56,135
<b>What is this?</b>

753
00:52:57,905 --> 00:52:58,935
<b>This woman...</b>

754
00:52:59,465 --> 00:53:00,875
<b>That's right. It's Yeo Ha Jin.</b>

755
00:53:01,006 --> 00:53:03,036
<b>She was a close friend
of Jung Seo Yeon.</b>

756
00:53:03,705 --> 00:53:05,105
<b>Lee Jeong Hoon...</b>

757
00:53:07,175 --> 00:53:08,846
<b>is dating this woman right now?</b>

758
00:53:09,046 --> 00:53:10,445
<b>It's nothing serious.</b>

759
00:53:10,445 --> 00:53:12,346
<b>They're going to break up anyway,</b>

760
00:53:12,516 --> 00:53:15,115
<b>but I got annoyed
when I had to watch him date her.</b>

761
00:53:15,256 --> 00:53:18,125
<b>This can't be.
They can't be together, you know.</b>

762
00:53:18,125 --> 00:53:19,125
<b>So what?</b>

763
00:53:20,395 --> 00:53:22,296
<b>What is it that you want from me?</b>

764
00:53:24,165 --> 00:53:25,996
<b>I want you to tell me...</b>

765
00:53:26,965 --> 00:53:29,496
<b>everything you did
to Lee Jeong Hoon.</b>

766
00:53:31,205 --> 00:53:34,476
<b>That way, he'll get scared and
stay away from my Ha Jin quickly.</b>

767
00:53:36,645 --> 00:53:38,746
<b>And you can get your revenge
against Lee Jeong Hoon too.</b>

768
00:53:40,076 --> 00:53:41,145
<b>Isn't that a win-win?</b>

769
00:53:57,996 --> 00:53:59,096
<b>I like it.</b>

770
00:54:00,465 --> 00:54:01,635
<b>That sounds fun.</b>

771
00:54:19,885 --> 00:54:22,385
<b>(Inmate Moon Seong Ho)</b>

772
00:54:29,125 --> 00:54:31,566
<b>So are you going
to start afresh with Yeo Ha Jin?</b>

773
00:54:37,736 --> 00:54:39,236
<b>I can't let you do that.</b>

774
00:54:44,905 --> 00:54:45,905
<b>Here.</b>

775
00:54:47,675 --> 00:54:50,046
<b>Now, tell me. What is this about?</b>

776
00:54:52,046 --> 00:54:53,046
<b>What do you mean?</b>

777
00:54:53,046 --> 00:54:56,385
<b>You keep saying you're fine today,
but I can tell you're sad.</b>

778
00:54:56,385 --> 00:54:57,756
<b>What's wrong?</b>

779
00:55:03,766 --> 00:55:05,195
<b>Are you still scared?</b>

780
00:55:06,465 --> 00:55:08,195
<b>Are you still anxious?</b>

781
00:55:08,596 --> 00:55:09,596
<b>Is that it?</b>

782
00:55:10,465 --> 00:55:13,276
<b>It's all over now.
You don't have to worry now.</b>

783
00:55:15,836 --> 00:55:18,276
<b>I think it's really over now.</b>

784
00:55:19,076 --> 00:55:20,076
<b>What?</b>

785
00:55:21,246 --> 00:55:22,976
<b>I think I have become...</b>

786
00:55:24,046 --> 00:55:26,185
<b>his past to Anchor Lee now.</b>

787
00:55:29,855 --> 00:55:32,086
<b>He had been nice to me
all this time...</b>

788
00:55:32,086 --> 00:55:33,996
<b>because of the stalker.</b>

789
00:55:35,695 --> 00:55:37,566
<b>Now, he doesn't need
to worry about me.</b>

790
00:55:39,996 --> 00:55:42,365
<b>I'm afraid he might leave me again
and wish me happiness.</b>

791
00:55:43,665 --> 00:55:46,365
<b>Is that why you didn't call him
and have been moping around all day?</b>

792
00:55:47,605 --> 00:55:48,605
<b>Yes.</b>

793
00:55:49,375 --> 00:55:50,605
<b>I'm afraid.</b>

794
00:55:53,816 --> 00:55:55,276
<b>Why don't we get some fresh air?</b>

795
00:55:58,086 --> 00:55:59,915
<b>Doesn't it feel suffocating
to stay indoors?</b>

796
00:56:00,115 --> 00:56:01,115
<b>Let's go for a walk.</b>

797
00:56:03,286 --> 00:56:04,286
<b>Okay.</b>

798
00:56:10,865 --> 00:56:12,625
<b>This feels nice.</b>

799
00:56:12,625 --> 00:56:14,865
<b>The view here is
better than I thought.</b>

800
00:56:17,205 --> 00:56:19,766
<b>How do you feel? Do you feel
better with some fresh air?</b>

801
00:56:19,836 --> 00:56:20,836
<b>Yes.</b>

802
00:56:21,336 --> 00:56:23,645
<b>I think I'll feel much better
with some tteokbokki.</b>

803
00:56:23,645 --> 00:56:25,445
<b>What are you talking about?
No tteokbokki.</b>

804
00:56:25,445 --> 00:56:27,415
<b>- How about fried chicken?
- No fried chicken.</b>

805
00:56:27,715 --> 00:56:29,945
<b>My gosh, I feel so sad.</b>

806
00:56:29,945 --> 00:56:32,286
<b>You feel sad?
Fresh air will lift your spirit.</b>

807
00:56:32,286 --> 00:56:33,915
<b>It's chilly here.
Let me get some blankets.</b>

808
00:56:33,915 --> 00:56:35,016
<b>Just order some food for me.</b>

809
00:56:35,016 --> 00:56:36,855
<b>How about a run around here?
It'll put us in a good mood.</b>

810
00:56:36,855 --> 00:56:37,855
<b>Get the blanket.</b>

811
00:56:37,855 --> 00:56:39,986
<b>Okay. I'll be quick. Wait here.</b>

812
00:56:53,705 --> 00:56:54,935
<b>You're back already?</b>

813
00:56:58,346 --> 00:56:59,776
<b>Are you feeling okay?</b>

814
00:57:00,516 --> 00:57:02,615
<b>I didn't call you because I wanted
you to rest up without distractions.</b>

815
00:57:06,086 --> 00:57:08,355
<b>What is it? Did something happen?</b>

816
00:57:08,986 --> 00:57:12,455
<b>How could you not call me once today
after leaving me this morning?</b>

817
00:57:14,155 --> 00:57:15,996
<b>Do you know how long
I waited for your call?</b>

818
00:57:17,195 --> 00:57:21,465
<b>I see. I didn't think
that you'd be waiting for my call.</b>

819
00:57:22,435 --> 00:57:24,506
<b>I had to take care of something.
I was distracted.</b>

820
00:57:41,486 --> 00:57:42,816
<b>It's your birthday present.</b>

821
00:57:46,925 --> 00:57:48,655
<b>I didn't know what to get you.</b>

822
00:57:48,655 --> 00:57:50,596
<b>So it took me some time
to pick out a present for you.</b>

823
00:57:50,865 --> 00:57:52,895
<b>I hope you like it.</b>

824
00:57:55,266 --> 00:57:57,665
<b>You left to buy my present?</b>

825
00:57:58,665 --> 00:57:59,705
<b>Yes.</b>

826
00:58:02,476 --> 00:58:03,776
<b>Won't you open it?</b>

827
00:58:18,955 --> 00:58:20,796
<b>What are all these?</b>

828
00:58:21,125 --> 00:58:23,355
<b>You don't get to sleep well
because of your nightmares.</b>

829
00:58:23,826 --> 00:58:25,826
<b>They help you sleep better.</b>

830
00:58:26,226 --> 00:58:28,465
<b>I wanted you to sleep well
without any nightmares.</b>

831
00:58:31,705 --> 00:58:33,605
<b>Picking out one was harder,</b>

832
00:58:33,605 --> 00:58:35,236
<b>so I decided to go for the quantity.</b>

833
00:58:39,776 --> 00:58:41,915
<b>What is it? Do you not like them?</b>

834
00:58:44,385 --> 00:58:46,246
<b>No, I like them.</b>

835
00:58:47,955 --> 00:58:50,425
<b>I was touched. I'm very thankful.</b>

836
00:58:51,556 --> 00:58:54,296
<b>But you don't look like
you're touched.</b>

837
00:58:55,056 --> 00:58:57,695
<b>I'm really touched, but...</b>

838
00:58:58,195 --> 00:58:59,195
<b>But?</b>

839
00:59:00,336 --> 00:59:01,665
<b>I'm afraid...</b>

840
00:59:03,536 --> 00:59:05,105
<b>that this might be the end.</b>

841
00:59:06,905 --> 00:59:09,976
<b>We started this because
of my one-sided crush on you.</b>

842
00:59:11,246 --> 00:59:13,476
<b>And then, we realized
there was a stalker.</b>

843
00:59:15,415 --> 00:59:17,286
<b>You were worried about me,</b>

844
00:59:17,286 --> 00:59:20,286
<b>so you were taking care of me
in case something happened to me.</b>

845
00:59:22,756 --> 00:59:24,655
<b>But now that he's arrested,</b>

846
00:59:26,786 --> 00:59:28,655
<b>it's really over.</b>

847
00:59:32,865 --> 00:59:34,536
<b>I'm scared that
you'll be nice to the end...</b>

848
00:59:34,536 --> 00:59:37,066
<b>and say goodbye
like the other time.</b>

849
00:59:40,875 --> 00:59:43,375
<b>Is that what this is?</b>

850
00:59:49,445 --> 00:59:51,046
<b>I won't say goodbye to you.</b>

851
00:59:53,346 --> 00:59:55,715
<b>I won't be saying goodbye
to you from now on.</b>

852
00:59:59,026 --> 01:00:00,026
<b>Why not?</b>

853
01:00:03,195 --> 01:00:05,096
<b>I want to stay by your side now.</b>

854
01:00:09,395 --> 01:00:11,405
<b>So you don't have to worry.</b>

855
01:00:19,246 --> 01:00:21,016
<b>You can't take that back.</b>

856
01:00:24,215 --> 01:00:25,645
<b>That's a promise, okay?</b>

857
01:00:27,816 --> 01:00:28,955
<b>I promise you.</b>

858
01:00:43,665 --> 01:00:44,935
<b>Happy birthday.</b>

859
01:02:04,546 --> 01:02:06,715
<b>(Find Me in Your Memory)</b>

860
01:02:06,816 --> 01:02:08,756
<b>What were you doing?
Were you thinking about me?</b>

861
01:02:08,756 --> 01:02:10,655
<b>Square your shoulders.</b>

862
01:02:10,855 --> 01:02:12,455
<b>Straighten your back.</b>

863
01:02:12,455 --> 01:02:13,955
<b>We should have a proper first date.</b>

864
01:02:13,955 --> 01:02:15,556
<b>Let's officially go on a date
this weekend.</b>

865
01:02:15,556 --> 01:02:17,226
<b>People will recognize us.</b>

866
01:02:17,226 --> 01:02:19,425
<b>They can watch us if they want.
We don't have to hide.</b>

867
01:02:19,425 --> 01:02:22,296
<b>How could you meet someone new
as if it's not a big deal?</b>

868
01:02:22,296 --> 01:02:23,766
<b>That's why it's fate.</b>

869
01:02:23,766 --> 01:02:25,836
<b>We are destined
to meet and fall in love.</b>

870
01:02:25,836 --> 01:02:27,605
<b>Because of you, Ha Jin's memory
might come back.</b>

871
01:02:27,605 --> 01:02:30,135
<b>I don't want to regret
any of the time I have left.</b>

872
01:02:30,135 --> 01:02:31,506
<b>What are you thinking?</b>

873
01:02:31,506 --> 01:02:32,905
<b>Grant me a wish too.</b>

874
01:02:32,905 --> 01:02:34,945
<b>Whatever situation we may be in,</b>

875
01:02:34,945 --> 01:02:37,415
<b>let's never say
goodbye to each other.</b>

